Actually, that's one of the hardest questions in the world.  At least,
the first question (What are numbers?) is.  

The second one is somewhat easier:  We have numbers for two reasons. 
First, because mathematicians like playing with them:

  http://mathforum.org/library/drmath/view/52350.html

And second, because they're useful for modeling the world:

  http://mathforum.org/library/drmath/view/61551.html

Does this help? 

